# Kotlin conventions

## Module boundaries

| Module | Rule |
|--------|------|
| `domain` | Pure Kotlin — no `android.*`, no JNI |
| `session-io`, `mixer-behringer` | JVM libraries — no Android APIs |
| `usb-audio`, `remote-server` | Android libraries — no Compose |
| `app` | Composition root — UI, service, wiring only |

Never import `app` from a library module.

## Patterns

- Shared state for UI + remote → add types in `domain` first
- Long-running audio → `AudioSessionService` / `MixerSessionController`, not Activity lifecycle alone
- USB probe channel count → `RecordingChannels` (max `AudioConstants.MAX_CHANNELS`, 64) — do not hardcode 2 or 18
- Coroutines for I/O and OSC; never block the Oboe callback thread from Kotlin

## Scope

- Match existing naming and style in the file you edit
- No drive-by refactors in unrelated modules
- Minimal diff — solve the task, don't reorganize

